Steps.Message: Update at 12:55 - Our engineers have arrived on site and are investigating the fault. You may find your power is going on and off; that is normal for this type of issue and is due to our engineers working to divert power remotely. By doing this, we've managed to restore power to 167 customers. There are now 205 properties still affected and using an average timeframe we're estimating all power will be on between 13:30 and 14:30, but this may change later depending on what our staff find. Please follow the government pandemic guidelines about social distancing when interacting with our staff. We'll keep sending SMS updates until everybody is restored. To stop receiving texts, send CANCEL to 80876 (standard fees apply).

We became aware of this power cut at 12:11. We’re sorry for any disruption this may have caused you. We didn’t know in advance there would be a power cut, but now that we know, our teams will do everything they can to get your power back quickly. Engineers in our control room have switched some customers power back on in your area. To get everyone’s power back on we may need to attend to investigate and make repairs. We’ll continue to update you until everyone’s power is back on.
Steps.Name: We are restoring customers automatically
